<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17450424-17">
               <interp inst="t17450424-17" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17450424-17" type="year" value="1745"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17450424-17" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17450424"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17450424-17" type="date" value="17450424"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17450424-17-off98-c160" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-defend190 t17450424-17-off98 t17450424-17-verdict101"></join>
         
               <p>208. 
               
                  <persName id="t17450424-17-defend190" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Hallam 
                  <interp inst="t17450424-17-defend190" type="surname" value="Hallam"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-defend190" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-defend190" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             of <placeName id="t17450424-17-defloc97">St. James Westminster</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17450424-17-defloc97" type="placeName" value="St. James Westminster"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17450424-17-defloc97" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-defend190 t17450424-17-defloc97"></join> , was indicted for <rs id="t17450424-17-off98" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-off98" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-off98" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing three shoes, val. 6 s.
            </rs> the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17450424-17-victim192" type="victimName">
                     Richard 
                     Bell 
                  <interp inst="t17450424-17-victim192" type="surname" value="Bell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-victim192" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-victim192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-off98 t17450424-17-victim192"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17450424-17-cd99" type="crimeDate">April 16th</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-off98 t17450424-17-cd99"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17450424-17-person193">
                  Richard 
                  Bell 
               <interp inst="t17450424-17-person193" type="surname" value="Bell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-person193" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-person193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner took these three shoes out of my shop; I had them at a pawnbroker's; the prisoner is a <rs id="t17450424-17-deflabel100" type="occupation">shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-defend190 t17450424-17-deflabel100"></join>, he has been in my shop a great many times, and I never missed any thing before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17450424-17-person194">
                  Thomas 
                  Parry 
               <interp inst="t17450424-17-person194" type="surname" value="Parry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-person194" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-person194" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner brought these shoes to my master's house to pawn, and I lent him 2 s. 6 d. upon them. I did not see there was an odd shoe till he was gone, then I thought they were stole; I called stop thief, and run after him; he owned he took them off the cutting board in the shop: but before the Justice, he said, he made them, and the reason of there being an odd shoe was, that he made one for a gouty foot. <rs id="t17450424-17-verdict101" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-verdict101" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-verdict101" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17450424-17-punish102" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-punish102" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17450424-17-punish102" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-17-defend190 t17450424-17-punish102"></join>
               
                     <note>[Whipping. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
